- Because the code explicitly specifies only RequestMethod.POST, only POST is accepted according to the source. No other handler in this controller (and no annotation in the provided code) exposes this path for other HTTP methods.
- @Secured({"ROLE_ADMIN"}) limits caller roles but does not change which HTTP methods are accepted.
- Although some servlet/framework behaviors (e.g., automatic handling of HEAD/OPTIONS) can occur at runtime, the answer above is derived strictly from the source code annotations and method signatures, per the requested constraint.
